comment: GSW inbounds the ball before a timeout is charged. Upon resumption of play, the ball was in-bounded on the sideline where play was interrupted.
Lee's (GSW) contact on Thompson (CLE) affects his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Lee (GSW) sets a screen on Dellavedova (CLE) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Lee (GSW) sets a screen on Dellavedova (CLE) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
James (CLE) cleanly strips the ball from Curry (GSW) before contact is made. The contact made after the strip is incidental to the players' attempt to retrieve the ball.
Lee (GSW) dives after the loose ball and lands on Dellavedova (CLE). Contact made is incidental in the players' attempt to retrieve the ball.
RATR shows Lee (GSW) grabs at the ball, making contact with Dellavedova's (CLE) head and upper body.
Thompson (GSW) commits a take foul on James (CLE).
James (CLE) requests a timeout away from the point of action and the request is not seen by officials.
Lee (GSW) sets a screen on Dellavedova (CLE) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Curry's (GSW) made field goal was taken from behind the three-point arc was upheld.
Thompson (GSW) commits a take foul on James (CLE).
RATR shows that Lee (GSW) gets into a legal screening position before the contact with Shumpert (CLE), but then grabs his leg and prevents him from recovering on defense.
Green (GSW) sets the screen on Thompson (CLE) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Mozgov (CLE) legally contests Curry's (GSW) jump shot and allows him to land. Any contact is initiated by Curry.

After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling that GSW be awarded the ball was overturned. Replay showed that Dellavedova (CLE) was inbounds and had possession when Thompson (GSW) made contact with the ball from OOBs. When the ball becomes OOBs because it is touching a player who is on or outside a boundary, such player is deemed to have caused it to go out. Possession by the player OOBs is not necessary.
Barnes (GSW) commits a take foul on James (CLE).
Lee (GSW) and Dellavedova (CLE) briefly engage then separate.
Smith (CLE) makes contact with Iguodala's (GSW) arm on his two-point shot attempt.
James (CLE) does not dislodge Green (GSW) during rebounding.
